data.name: Description.coords
data.value:
_List of XY coordinates which define the polygon of the area. 
rect: left-x, top-y, right-x, bottom-y. circle: center-x, center-y, radius. 
Note. When the radius value is a percentage value, user agents should calculate the final radius value based on the associated object's width and height. The radius should be the smaller value of the two. 
poly: x1, y1, x2, y2, ..., xN, yN. The first x and y coordinate pair and the last should be the same to close the polygon. When these coordinate values are not the same, user agents should infer an additional coordinate pair to close the polygon.
